    "\n",
    "## Key rules to carry forward {.smaller}\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Chain, don't soup** — one pipeline, zero intermediate variables\n",
    "2. **Always use `lambda`** in `.assign()` when referencing new columns\n",
    "3. **Never use `inplace=True`** — it breaks chains and returns `None`\n",
    "4. **Explicit plotting only** — `fig, ax = plt.subplots()`, always\n",
    "5. **Tidy before modeling** — each variable a column, each observation a row\n",
    "6. **Check `.dtypes` early** — `object` on a numeric column means trouble\n",
